All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable, Cloneable, Iterable<T>, Collection<T>, List<T>, RandomAccess, Restorable, InterfaceDeck<T>, Observable, Observer
public class Deck<T> extends AbstractDeck<T> implements Observable, Observer, Restorable
This class defines the deck for the game. The deck is a stack, from which it is possible to draw using the draw() method. When the deck is almost empty it is automatically filled with cards and shuffled. The deck notifies all its observers whenever a card is drawn.
Author:
Simone Gentili
